verses.roman:
tāṅra jhārī-śeṣāmṛta kichu more dilā
tateke bharila peṭa, tṛṣṇā mora gelā

synonyms: tāṅra jhārī-śeṣa-amṛta—the remnants of the milk of Vṛndāvana dāsa Ṭhākura's pitcher; kichu—some; more dilā—has given to me; tateke—by those remnants; bharila peṭa—my abdomen is filled; tṛṣṇā mora gelā—now my thirst has gone.
translation: Whatever remnants of milk Vṛndāvana dāsa Ṭhākura has given me are sufficient to fill my belly. Now my thirst is completely satiated.
